The Minister of State for Health,  Osagie Ehanire, says Nigeria is currently losing more than $1 billion dollar yearly to medical service sourced abroad by Nigerians. According to him, medical tourism is a declaration of no confidence in the nation’s health system, Ehanire said this yesterday in Benin during the University of Benin Teaching Hospital’s 46th founder’s day and launching of an endowment fund for the hospital. “About a year ago, it was estimated that Nigeria loses about $1billion every year to medical service sourced abroad. The figure is probably higher now. The medical tourism is a declaration of no confidence in our health system, which we must endeavour to address,” Nigeria loses $1b to medical tourism Why Nigeria loses $1bn on medical tourism – Minister Nizamiye Hospital aims to discourage medical tourism Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin